├── Planning and Requirements Gathering/
│   ├── Define scope and objectives
│   ├── Identify tools and technologies
│   ├── Set up GitHub repository for version control
│   └── Create high-level architecture diagram
├── Infrastructure (via Terraform)/
│   ├── Step 2.1: Setup Terraform Environment/
│   │   ├── Install Terraform locally
│   │   ├── Configure backend and state management (Redis)
│   └── Step 2.2: Provision EC2 Instances/
│       ├── Write Terraform scripts to provision EC2
│       ├── Configure SSH access and security groups
│   ├── Step 2.3: Kubernetes Setup/
│   │   ├── Deploy Kubernetes cluster on EC2
│   │   ├── Integrate with Terraform scripts
│   │   └── Configure network settings
│   ├── Step 2.4: Deploy Redis Database/
│   │   ├── Provision Redis via Terraform
│   │   └── Configure Redis for user data and Terraform state
│   ├── Step 2.5: S3 Bucket Configuration/
│   │   ├── Set up S3 bucket via Terraform
│   │   └── Implement bucket policies and IAM roles
│   └── Step 2.6: Ingress Load Balancer/
│       └── Deploy and configure Ingress controller
├── Application Deployment/
│   ├── Step 3.1: Deploy FE Application/
│   │   ├── Set up Nginx server in Kubernetes
│   │   └── Manage deployment with Helm
│   ├── Step 3.2: Configure SFTP Server/
│   │   ├── Deploy SFTP server in Kubernetes
│   │   └── Automate email notifications and monitoring
│   ├── Step 3.3: Helm Configurations/
│   │   ├── Create Helm charts for deployment
│   │   └── Manage ConfigMaps and mount JSON files
│   └── Step 3.4: Python Scripts for Monitoring and Parsing/
│       ├── Write and deploy Python scripts for JSON parsing
│       └── Automate monitoring tasks with Python
├── Local Development and CI/CD Setup/
│   ├── Step 4.1: Set Up Jenkins Server/
│   │   ├── Install and configure Jenkins
│   │   └── Create CI/CD pipelines
│   ├── Step 4.2: Docker Image Building/
│   │   ├── Write Dockerfiles for components
│   │   └── Automate image building and push to DockerHub
│   └── Step 4.3: Public GitHub Repository/
│       ├── Host project code on GitHub
│       └── Integrate with Jenkins for CI/CD
├── Enhancements/
│   ├── Step 5.1: Security Hardening/
│   │   ├── Implement IAM roles and security groups
│   │   └── Manage Secrets in Kubernetes
│   ├── Step 5.2: Monitoring and Logging/
│   │   ├── Set up Prometheus for monitoring
│   │   └── Deploy ELK stack for logging
│   ├── Step 5.3: High Availability and Scaling/
│   │   ├── Enable auto-scaling for EC2 and Kubernetes
│   │   └── Set up multi-AZ deployments
│   └── Step 5.4: Backup and Disaster Recovery/
│       ├── Configure Redis and S3 backups
│       └── Implement disaster recovery procedures
├── Documentation/
│   ├── Step 6.1: Infrastructure Documentation/
│   │   ├── Document setup and architecture
